ASUS has unveiled its latest gaming mouse, the ROG Gladius II. The device has a detachable wired connection, allowing users to switch between braided and rubber cables. A DPI button below the mouseâ€™s scroll wheel lets gamers control sensitivity on the fly, and the device has two buttons on its left side. The ROG Gladius II Origin also sports three RGB lighting zones and a 12,000 DPI sensor. The mouse is available now in the US and is priced at $100.  